/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/refined/chain-03.md:133:- shows cleanly that the exact coupled invariant geometry is too non-coercive or too fragile under full-equation restoration and localization to improve on known folklore.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attack is mostly right. The original chain has a real research instinct: it tries to test whether full 3D energy-helicity transport contains theorem-relevant structure that is not visible in energy-only or same-helicity-only viewpoints. That is a legitimate target. But the attack correctly identifies the main danger: the chain treats joint energy-helicity flux as if it were already near a coercive mechanism, when in practice helicity is sign-indefinite, cancellation-prone, and hard to localize.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:7:The refined version should therefore remain open to a positive route only under a much harder admission standard. The default working hypothesis should be that the exact coupled invariant geometry is non-coercive unless the branch can exhibit one one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain early.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:14:The attack is right that the original Step 1 froze the endpoint and invariant package too early, and it is right that the package menu was too heterogeneous to treat as a single neutral choice. It is also right that the minimum gain standard needed to name one explicit bad term or exclusion pattern. But some early freezing is still good method. The fix is to freeze guardrails and admissibility standards first, while delaying the final endpoint lock until a candidate one-sided gain survives an initial coercivity screen.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:19:This is a strong criticism. Exact coupled identities are cheap compared with the real burden, which is to show that some coupled quantity survives sign restoration, localization, and ordinary inequality losses without collapsing back to energy-only control. The attack is also correct that the Tao comparator was too underspecified and too easy to backfill from a favorable decomposition.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:24:The attack is correct that this is the decisive step and the original chain did not operationalize the threshold sharply enough. A promoted mechanism must do more than narrate favorable polarized sectors. It must identify how a joint energy-helicity feature reduces one named bad term or excludes one named bad transfer pattern in a quantitatively relevant portion of the full nonlinear burden.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/judgments/chain-03.md:29:The attack is right that mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, and localization are not late restoration costs. They are architecture-defining constraints for this branch. The original chain named these debts, which is good, but treated them too much as downstream reconstruction rather than as early viability screens.
