+### Scope-Lock Answers
+
+#### 1. Endpoint burden family
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Freeze the provisional burden family as `stretching/enstrophy bottleneck`.
+- Support:
+  `GOAL.md` and `CHAIN.md` require one burden-family freeze and explicitly list `stretching/enstrophy bottleneck` as one admissible family.
+  `winning-chain.md` and `CHAIN.md` then make theorem relevance depend on reaching one named bad term or bad transfer pattern and repeatedly name `stretching production` and `enstrophy growth` as the Step-2 burden language.
+  `judgments/chain-03.md` and `attacks/chain-03.md` both reject vague continuation-style restatements and require a quantitatively relevant reduction of one named bad term or exclusion of one named bad transfer pattern.
+- Why this is the least rhetorical choice:
+  `continuation criterion` remains too easy to collapse into a BKM-style restatement.
+  `concentration exclusion` is mentioned as a menu option but is less directly tied to the named bad-term list on the run-007 record.
+  `stretching/enstrophy bottleneck` is the only family repeatedly connected to one named bad term and one quantitative burden share.
+
+#### 2. Invariant package
+
+- `[INFERRED]` Freeze the first audit package as `dyadic coupled fluxes`.
+- Support:
+  `GOAL.md`, `CHAIN.md`, `selected/chain-03.md`, and `winning-chain.md` all allow `dyadic coupled fluxes` explicitly.
+  `planner.md` describes Chain 03 as `invariant and cascade-facing`, which is more naturally matched to dyadic transfer bookkeeping than to generic coarse-grained balance-law language.
+  The receptionist packet concludes that the on-disk support is more triad/dyadic than balance-law generic.
+- Limitation:
+  `[VERIFIED]` no dedicated on-disk energy/helicity identity sheet was found for this package. The record supports the package choice only indirectly through chain instructions and exact-NS helical/triad materials. This weakens enforceability.
+
+#### 3. Tao-sensitive feature
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The most concrete Step-1 Tao-sensitive feature is:
+  exact role-labeled helical packet coupling, with mandatory conjugate completion and frozen sign/amplitude/phase packet-sheet data, tested against whether it can realize a Tao-like five-role delayed-threshold circuit without spectator leakage.
+- Why this feature is concrete enough now:
+  `tao-likeness-requires-a-five-part-canonicalization-screen.md` gives an operational Tao screen: five packet roles, ordered delayed-threshold sequence, dominant-channel hierarchy, sign/phase bookkeeping, and bounded spectator leakage.
+  `support-means-a-role-labeled-helical-packet-with-mandatory-conjugate-completion.md` fixes the smallest honest support object as a role-labeled helical packet with forced conjugate completion.
+  `helical-signs-amplitude-normalization-and-phase-anchor-belong-to-the-frozen-packet-sheet.md` requires explicit sign, amplitude, and phase anchors up front.
+  `atlas-anatomy-exploration-002-REPORT.md` and `atlas-anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall-FINAL-REPORT.md` identify the exact-NS mismatch as coefficient rigidity plus unavoidable spectator couplings, not generic multiscale sparsity.
+- Passing/failing calibration implication:
+  A packet family passes only if it survives the five-part Tao canonicalization screen.
+  A packet family fails if it reduces to sparse/triad-engineered folklore or if exact NS forces spectator/conjugate couplings that destroy the delayed-threshold role hierarchy.
+
+#### 4. Frozen baseline criterion
+
+- `[INFERRED]` The strongest baseline the record supports is:
+  later steps must beat the default `exact but non-coercive` stretching/enstrophy bottleneck baseline by naming one explicit one-sided gain on stretching production, enstrophy growth, or one equally explicit bad transfer pattern in the same burden language.
+- Support:
+  `CHAIN.md` and `winning-chain.md` make non-coercivity the default hypothesis and require one named bad term or bad transfer pattern.
+  `judgments/chain-03.md` requires a promoted mechanism to reduce one named bad term or exclude one named bad transfer pattern in a quantitatively relevant portion of the full nonlinear burden.
+  `attacks/chain-03.md` rejects any baseline phrased only as attractive cascade language.
+- Obstruction:
+  `[VERIFIED]` this baseline is still burden-language, not yet one explicit inequality, exclusion statement, or contradiction line. The local record freezes the burden type but not the exact mathematical cash-out.
+
+#### 5. Minimum quantitative gain threshold
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The local record does not support a sharper numeric threshold.
+- `[INFERRED]` The minimum meaningful threshold still visible on disk is:
+  a strictly positive, one-sided improvement on the named stretching/enstrophy bad term or forbidden transfer pattern that still survives mixed-helicity restoration, low-helicity regions, pressure, viscosity, and localization on a quantitatively relevant burden share.
+- Support:
+  `GOAL.md` and `CHAIN.md` require the threshold to survive localization, pressure, viscosity, and mixed-helicity debt.
+  `judgments/chain-03.md` requires a quantitatively relevant portion of the full nonlinear burden.
+  `attacks/chain-03.md` explicitly says that “would change the endpoint” is too soft and that Step 1 needs an explicit reduction of one named bad term or exclusion pattern.
+- Obstruction:
+  `[VERIFIED]` no on-disk source freezes the gain currency tightly enough to distinguish a real threshold from “positive margin somehow.” Under the step failure criteria, that is not concrete enough.
+
+#### 6. Admission rule and novelty rule
+
+- `[PROPOSED]` Admission rule for Step 2 mechanical enforcement:
+  reject every candidate unless it names:
+  one dyadic coupled-flux observable or forbidden transfer pattern,
+  one named stretching-production or enstrophy-growth burden,
+  one claimed one-sided sign/exclusion gain on that burden,
+  one declared burden share,
+  and one statement that survives the Tao screen plus mixed-helicity, pressure, viscosity, and localization debt.
+- Support:
+  `CHAIN.md` already gives the core admission rule.
+  `judgments/chain-03.md` adds the need for a quantitatively relevant portion of the full nonlinear burden.
+  `GOAL.md` demands language that later steps can enforce mechanically.
+
+- `[PROPOSED]` Novelty rule for Step 2 mechanical enforcement:
+  reject every candidate that earns leverage only from favorable same-helicity or polarized sectors unless the candidate is written on a role-labeled packet with mandatory conjugate completion and frozen packet-sheet data, and it proves that this sector carries a quantitatively relevant share of the full dyadic stretching/enstrophy burden after mixed-helicity restoration.
+- Support:
+  `CHAIN.md` gives the same-helicity burden-share rule.
+  `attacks/chain-03.md` and `judgments/chain-03.md` both require prior-art screening before promotion and reject thin favorable sectors.
+  The packet-policy factual files make the support object and packet-sheet declarations explicit enough to audit.
+
+#### 7. Does the local record support a real scope lock?
+
+- `[VERIFIED]` The record supports a narrowed setup, not a fully earned scope lock.
+- What is actually supported:
+  one best burden family,
+  one best first package,
+  one concrete Tao-sensitive feature family,
+  and mechanically enforceable admission/novelty rules.
+- What remains missing:
+  one dedicated exact dyadic energy/helicity identity sheet on disk,
+  one explicit baseline inequality/exclusion statement,
+  and one gain threshold with a frozen quantitative currency rather than “positive margin after debts.”
+- Result:
+  the local record supports a narrowed configuration plus explicit collapse warnings, not a Step-2-ready lock.
